Xiaomi’s mid-range offering is fast gaining global attention and taking consumers by storm. The brand announced over 250,000,000 users globally in March this year, this equates to around 1/3 of the population in Europe. With this popularity, the Redmi Note Series has undoubtedly proven to be a leader in the segment, and an entry level smartphone that deeply resonates with consumers. Redmi Note Series: Consistently surprising consumers What makes this series so popular across the globe? Let’s look at how the series has evolved in the past few years. In 2019, flagship-level 48MP camera was introduced to Redmi Note 7, which raised the bar in terms of photography. The market was then introduced to Redmi Note 8 Series, Xiaomi brought the first 64MP smartphone camera to the series. The Redmi Note 9 Series’ 33W fast charging is featured to achieve more efficient charging experience. Fast forward all the way to 2021, Redmi Note 10 Series offered users a delight with the whopping 108MP main camera, gaining the device industry praise.  Built with innovative technologies that surprised consumers in the segment, the Redmi Note 10 Series bagged multiple prestigious awards in 2021 such as the Trusted Reviews Awards. “The Xiaomi Redmi Note 10 Pro manages to stand out in a crowded budget smartphone field thanks to a stunning 120Hz AMOLED display and a capable 108MP camera.” wrote mobile reviewer Jon Mundy in his review on Redmi Note 10 Pro.  Redmi Note 11 Series: “Rise to the challenge” again This year, the Redmi Note 11 Series was launched in Nigeria and many other Africa markets. Like its slogan, The Redmi Note 11 Series rose to the challenge with further technology breakthroughs like 120W fast charging, flagship-level 108MP main camera, and impressive 120Hz AMOLED display.  Redmi Note 11 Pro+ 5G is the first ever Redmi Note smartphone equipped with 120W charging, capable of charging the massive 4,500mAh battery to 100% in just 15 minutes, which makes this device a “charging monster”. Meanwhile, the 67W turbo charging in Redmi Note 11 Pro, takes as little as 15 minutes to fill 50% of the battery. Redmi Note 11S and Redmi Note 11 feature 33W Pro fast charging, allowing you to charge to 100% in an hour. Consistently proving to be a leader in its segment, the Redmi Note 11 Pro+ 5G, Redmi Note 11 Pro, and Redmi Note 11S have raised the flagship camera experience with the 108MP primary sensors. Perfect for capturing moments with true-to-life detail. The Redmi Note 11 series is great for enhancing screen experience and lag free transitions thanks to a high refresh rate up to 120Hz and a touch sampling rate up to 360Hz.  Innovate for everyone In a most fiercely competitive market, Redmi Note Series’ success proved it is a series that can truly satisfy what people really need today. It also embodies how Xiaomi “Innovate for everyone”. Specs of Redmi Note 11 Series 